        "type": "msgpack",
        "blob": "message_id$24c2cac0-1671-4200-9754-107878c9f0c1roleusercontentHow Neural Networks workstimestamp2026-02-07T21:55:56.161127message_idmsg_1770537360.846603roleassistantcontent\u0002^Neural networks are a type of machine learning model inspired by the human brain. (IBM, AWS, Khan Academy, Reddit). They work by processing data through layers of interconnected \"neurons\" or nodes (IBM, GeeksforGeeks, Reddit). Each neuron takes an input, applies a weight and bias, and passes the result to the next layer (IBM, Reddit). The network learns by adjusting these weights and biases to recognize patterns and map inputs to desired outputs (IBM). This process of learning from data enables neural networks to perform tasks like image recognition, natural language processing, and more (IBM, AWS).timestamp2026-02-08T02:56:00.846664message_typetext"
